    "long_instructions": "# Do This:\r\n\r\nHelp! There's something wrong with the program! It isn't doing exactly what it should be according to the algorithm flowchart below. \r\n1. Read through the flowchart to understand what the program should do. <br>\r\n2. Run and test the program to debug the program so that it works as expected for all outcomes.<br>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://images.code.org/5b9333200c988348fd80197ff2504404-Screenshot 2025-02-07 094249.png\" style=\"width:300px;\">\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## AI Tutor Support:\r\n\r\n::: details [**Not sure why the program isn't following the flowchart?**]\r\n\r\n**Ask AI:**\r\n- If you're unsure why the Painter isn’t behaving as expected, use AI Tutor to investigate how nested conditionals affect the outcome.\r\n- If you're having trouble debugging incorrect logic, ask AI for help analyzing errors.\r\n:::",
    "start_sources": {
      "files": {
        "0": {
          "id": "0",
          "name": "main.py",
          "language": "py",
          "contents": "import unittest\nfrom unittest_runner import ValidationProtocol\n\nclass TestDebugFlowerCode(unittest.TestCase):\n    @classmethod\n    def setUpClass(cls):\n        \"\"\"\n        Retrieve the NeighborhoodLog once for all tests.\n        \"\"\"\n        cls.log = ValidationProtocol().get_neighborhood_log()\n        painter_logs = cls.log.painter_logs if cls.log else []\n        cls.painter_log = painter_logs[0] if painter_logs else None\n\n    def test_step1_single_painter_mary(self):\n        \"\"\"\n        Create a Painter object.\n        \"\"\"\n        self.assertIsNotNone(\n            self.painter_log,\n            \"No Painter object found.\"\n        )\n        painter_count = len(self.log.painter_logs)\n        self.assertEqual(\n            painter_count,\n            1,\n            f\"Found {painter_count} Painters instead of exactly one.\"\n        )\n\n    def test_step2_turn_right_used(self):\n        \"\"\"\n        The Painter turns right.\n        \"\"\"\n        if self.painter_log is None:\n            self.skipTest(\"No Painter found.\")\n\n        turn_left_count = self.painter_log.action_count(\"TURN_LEFT\")\n        self.assertGreaterEqual(\n            turn_left_count,\n            3,\n            \"We expected at least 3 'TURN_LEFT' actions to turn right. \"\n            \"Double-check your turn_right() function call.\"\n        )\n\n    def test_step3_moved_at_least_once(self):\n        \"\"\"\n        The Painter moves at least once.\n        \"\"\"\n        if self.painter_log is None:\n            self.skipTest(\"No Painter found.\")\n\n        self.assertTrue(\n            self.painter_log.did_action_at_least(\"MOVE\", 1),\n            \"Your Painter never moved. Did you call move_if_can() or move in paint_flower()?\"\n        )\n\n    def test_step4_painted_at_least_once(self):\n        \"\"\"\n        Paint at least once.\n        \"\"\"\n        if self.painter_log is None:\n            self.skipTest(\"No Painter found.\")\n\n        self.assertTrue(\n            self.painter_log.did_action_at_least(\"PAINT\", 1),\n            \"We don't see any paint actions.\"\n        )\n",
          "folderId": "0",
          "active": true,
          "open": true
        }
      },
      "folders": {
      }
